The immigration , ? a burden or a opportunity for the economy ?
The policy of immigration roundly by Nicolas Sarkozy has been criticada that since various points of view : the saturación of the services police , judicial and administrative subject to the policy of figures , the doubts of this policy with the status autoproclamado of &apos; country of the rights human &apos; of France .
than recently , is the harassment administrative of the students foreign the that has saltado to the headlines , with the Minister of Interior ( véase the newspaper Libération the 23 of May ) proclamando of last that France &apos; not needs talentos foreign , workers or camareros &apos; .
, however , rarely time . analysing since the point of view economic .
The question is that , on this issue , there quite consensus between the left and the right .
In the case of the right , Jacques Chirac fijó the it declarando in 1976 that &apos; 900.000 unemployed not should be a problem for a country that account with close of two million of workers immigrants &apos; , while that in the left , the tone what fijó Michel Rocard explicando that France &apos; not can done office of whole the misery the world &apos; in 1990 .
The only difference , the degree of generosity
In 2005 , therefore the left as the right compartían the fear to the invasion the territory national by a a of fontaneros Poles .
. both both , . as that the immigrants are a burden for the economy and the society French .
The only difference is in the degree of generosity with the that act with regard to the immigrants .
In their programme , &apos; Hollande . limited to include banalidades , those that the codesarrollo will right the &apos; problem of the migration &apos; .
This idea of the immigration as a burden , a problem , perhaps is why electoralmente , but economically its very face .
As as guarding the economists Party Goldin and Geoffrey phase in a labour recent that sums the knowledge more recent on the immigration ( Exceptional People : How Migration Shaped Our World and Will Define Our Future , May of 2011 , Princeton University reporter , 352 pp . ) , there a broader consensus between the specialists on the impact positive of the flows migratory in the growth economic , the wages and the employment in the countries that receive immigrants .
The - of the immigration it the growth and also the employment .
The fears related with the impact of the immigrants . based in the idea of that these can replace to the workers national , in particular to the little qualified , pressing for that . reduce their wages .
But the experience shows that , in reality , the immigrants are more well additional that substitutes of the workers national and use mainly professions in sectors with lack of employment .
The immigrants little qualified working in sectors that not by to workers national and the more qualified in sectors dynamic where the training not This the demand of personal .
A effect positive on the wages
From same way that a surgeon would difficulties for work in a country that have lack of anestesistas , the complementariedad between national and immigrants from that the arrival of these last 8.4 welcome in the wages and the employment of the national .
mind in account what previous , Giovanni Peri calculó that a increase the 1 % of the flows migratory is a takes of the wages real to long term of between a 0,6 and a 0,9 % .
And , without have in account the fact of that the diversity that aportan the immigrants helps to the creation of ideas and the growth economic ( there a great proportion of prizes Nobel Americans naturalizados and companies as Google , Intel , Paypal , eBay and Yahoo were well-founded by immigrants ) .
The immigrants also are taxpayers dig to the systems social , since that aportan of average a 1 % the budget total in the countries European .
The Organisation International the Labour estimated , by example , that in Germany a immigrant that it with a age of 30 years operators a contribution neta ( income least expenses ) of 150.000 EUR to the budgets public of average for whole their life .
At principle of their mandate , Nicolas Sarkozy wanted go to to the points of growth that to faltaban &apos; with the European &apos; .
which European , that disuadieron to the immigrants , had exactly the effect reverse .
